    <XmlExtensions.SettingsMenuDef>
        <modId>com.protobeard.madagascarvanilla</modId>
        <label>Madagascar Vanilla</label>
        <settings>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Any changes require a restart to take effect.</text>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Gap"/>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Stand Your Ground</text>
                <tooltip>Set default pawn hostility response (vanilla is Flee).</tooltip>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.RadioButtons">
                <key>hostilityResponse</key>
                <defaultValue>Flee</defaultValue>
                <buttons>
                    <li>
                        <value>Ignore</value>
                        <label>Ignore</label>
                        </li>
                    <li>
                        <value>Attack</value>
                        <label>Attack</label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <value>Flee</value>
                        <label>Flee</label>
                    </li>
                </buttons>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Drugs</text>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>drugPolicy</key>
                <label>Just Say No</label>
                <tooltip>Set default pawn drug policy to "No Drugs" (vanilla is "Social Drugs").</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Acceptable Quest Rewards</text>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>goodwillRewards</key>
                <label>Allow Goodwill Rewards</label>
                <tooltip>Set default value of allow goodwill rewards from factions (vanilla is true).</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>true</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>royalFavorRewards</key>
                <label>Allow Honor as Reward</label>
                <tooltip>Set default value of allow honor as reward from factions (vanilla is true).</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>true</defaultValue>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Schedule Setup</text>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Gap"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Overrride the default RimWorld schedule with one that includes recreation, and has slightly less sleep so if pawns wake up early they don't go back to bed. Special trairs and gene modifiers can be enabled below. Regardless of modifications, all pawns will recreate at the same time to help with social relations. Note that children will be assigned recreation even though they don't technically need it (that way you don't have to touch their schedule when they reach adulthood).</text>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>initialSchedule</key>
                <label>Override Default Schedules</label>
                <tooltip>Set pawns up with a better initial schedule which includes recreation.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>initialNightOwlSchedule</key>
                <label>Special Night Owl Schedule</label>
                <tooltip>Set up Night Owl pawns with a better initial schedule that sleeps during the day and includes recreation at the same time as other pawns.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>initialUVSensitiveSchedule</key>
                <label>Special UV Sensitive Schedule</label>
                <tooltip>Set up pawns with UV sensitive genes (Dirtmoles, Sanguophages, etc.) with a better initial schedule that has sleeps during the day and includes recreation at the same time as other pawns.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>initialSleepyGeneSchedule</key>
                <label>Special Sleep Gene Schedules</label>
                <tooltip>Set up pawns that have sleep modifying genes (Very Sleepy, Sleepy, Low Sleep, Never Sleep) with better initial schedules that have appropriate sleep time and include recreation. Sleep and Very Sleepy pawns are given biphasic scheudules. Never Sleep pawns are given a schedule with no sleep time.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>initialBodyMasterySchedule</key>
                <label>Special Body Mastery Schedule</label>
                <tooltip>Set up Body Mastery pawns that with a better initial schedule that has no sleep time but includes recreation.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>reduceSleepForQuickSleepers</key>
                <label>Reduce Sleep in Schedules for Quick Sleepers</label>
                <tooltip>Reduce Sleep in Schedules for Quick Sleepers by ~ 1/3</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>true</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>avoidScheduledMoodDebuffs</key>
                <label>Avoid Scheduled Mood Debuffs</label>
                <tooltip>Do not reduce sleep in schedules for Night Owl/UV Sensitive even if the pawn has Quick Sleeper. This helps to prevent mood debuffs on those pawns for being awake during the day or in the sunlight. Body Mastery and Never Sleep schedules are not effected by this setting.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>true</defaultValue>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Plant Changes</text>
                <tooltip>All of these are off by default in vanilla.</tooltip>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>hydroponicDevilstrand</key>
                <label>Hydroponic Devilstrand</label>
                <tooltip>Devilstrand can be grown in hydroponic basins.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>falloutImmuneDevilstrand</key>
                <label>Toxic Fallout Immune Devilstrand</label>
                <tooltip>Devilstrand is immune to toxic fallout.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>falloutImmuneToxipotatos</key>
                <label>Toxic Fallout Immune Toxipotatos</label>
                <tooltip>Toxipotatos are immune to toxic fallout.</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Areas</text>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Comma separated list of areas to start a new game with (e.g., "Work,Inside,Safe"). Enter up to 10 areas, or leave field blank to use RimwWorld's default of "Area 1." If you area using a mod like Areas Unlimted or TD Enhancement Pack's unlimited areas option, enter as many areas as you would like.</text>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Textbox">
                <key>startingAreasList</key>
                <label>Starting Areas:</label>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Mechanitor Settings</text>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>enableMechRepair</key>
                <label>Enable Mech Repair by Default</label>
                <tooltip>Enable automatically repairing colony mechs by default (vanilla default is false).</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
                <key>nonflammableMechResourceChips</key>
                <label>Make all Mechanitor Chips Nonflammable</label>
                <tooltip>Make all mechanitor chips (signal, power focus, nano structuring) non flammable (vanilla default is only signal chips).</tooltip>
                <defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine"/>
            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>Odyssey Quests</text>
                <anchor>Middle</anchor>
            </li>


            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
                <text>For 100% worlds it can be nice to have additional time for Odyssey space site quests so that traveling around the world is not as punishing. You can also increase the distance at which these quests are located to further enhance the world traveling vibe (note that grav ship quests are not impacted as they can already appear far away from the colony).</text>
                <anchor>Left</anchor>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Numeric">
                <key>odysseyQuestExtensionMultipler</key>
                <label>Multiply Odyssey Quest Expiration Time by X (vanilla default is 1, I'd recommend 2-3 for a 100% world)</label>
                <defaultValue>1</defaultValue>
                <decimals>0</decimals>
                <min>1</min>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Range">
                <key>odysseyQuestRangeExtender</key>
                <label>Odyssey Quest Generation Distance (vanilla default is 1~3, I'd recommend 1~5 for a 100% world)</label>
                <defaultValue>1~3</defaultValue>
                <decimals>0</decimals>
                <min>1</min>
                <max>20</max>
            </li>

            <li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Numeric">
                <key>allowXAdditionalGravshipSubquests</key>
                <label>Allow X Gravship Subquests (vanilla default is 3)</label>
                <defaultValue>3</defaultValue>
                <decimals>0</decimals>
                <min>3</min>
            </li>


